Mpoke embraced athletics back in 2014 at Sosio High School in Narok where he competed in 200m and 400m. He transferred to Shartuka High School for hisÂ Form three and four classes."I failed to complete a race in 400m and our games teacher Cosmos Lagat told me to change to the hurdles,"said Mpoke, who never disappointed as he would win the 400m hurdles both at the national secondary school championships and the trials for 2017 World Under-18.